@wbrangham reports from Capitol Hill ⬇
・・・
USMC Lance Corporal Marisa Woytek testifying before Congress today, explaining how she's been threatened and harassed *even more* now that she's speaking out about the so-called "Marines United" scandal, where a Facebook group made up of thousands of current and former Marines were recently caught sharing explicit photos of female Marines (without their consent), along with an endless litany of sexually degrading and violent threats directed at the women. We're reporting on this story for @newshour.

@wbrangham reports for us from Parris Island, SC:
Weekly haircut for young male recruits at Marine Corps boot camp. (We're here for @newshour reporting how the Corps is integrating women into combat roles.) Women recruits can wear longer hair as long as it's tied tightly in a bun, but the men are required to get the weekly skin job.
